The paper deals with the automatic prediction of facial expressiveness from visual data, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). However, the paper also discusses the relationship between expressiveness and personality/mental health, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also mentions the potential applications of their work in artificial social intelligence, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper presents statistical models for predicting expressiveness, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
